text: Trapania miltabrancha is a species of sea slug, a dorid nudibranch, a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Goniodorididae.Bouchet, P. (2015). Trapania miltabrancha. In: MolluscaBase (2015). Accessed through: World Register of Marine Species on 2015-10-16 ==Distribution== This species was first described from Bali.Rudman, W.B., 2008 (March 10) Trapania miltabrancha Gosliner & Fahey, 2008. [In] Sea Slug Forum. Australian Museum, Sydney. It has subsequently been reported from the Philippines. ==Description== This goniodorid nudibranch has a complicated colour pattern. The body is a mosaic of brown patches which contain white spots, interspersed with orange. The rhinophores, lateral papillae and gills are cream with brown patches. ==Ecology== Trapania miltabrancha feeds on Entoprocta which often grow on sponges, algae and other living substrata.Trapania miltabrancha AgnipaScuba Diving, Tauchen, Lonos, Romblon Island, Philippines. ==References== Category:Goniodorididae Category:Gastropods described in 2008
title: Trapania miltabrancha
